1
00:00:09,500 --> 00:00:11,375
[CASSHERN]
I am Casshern.

2
00:00:12,791 --> 00:00:15,833
Luna... I will... kill you.

3
00:02:03,333 --> 00:02:06,166
[GAMBLERBOT A] Yes!
A royal straight flush!

4
00:02:06,250 --> 00:02:08,625
[IMPACT]

5
00:02:08,708 --> 00:02:10,166
[GAMBLERBOT C]
Damn you!

6
00:02:10,250 --> 00:02:13,375
[CLANKING METAL]

7
00:02:13,458 --> 00:02:14,500
[GAMBLERBOT C]
I knew it you stinkin' cheat,

8
00:02:14,583 --> 00:02:15,708
I knew it!

9
00:02:15,791 --> 00:02:21,250
[GAMBLERBOT C YELLING
AND METAL CLANKING]

10
00:02:21,333 --> 00:02:24,291
Royal straight flush.

11
00:02:24,375 --> 00:02:26,041
[GAMBLERBOT B] Great, now
we're short a player.

12
00:02:26,125 --> 00:02:28,083
There goes the game.

13
00:02:29,708 --> 00:02:32,291
[GAMBLERBOT B
GASPS IN AMAZEMENT]

14
00:02:32,375 --> 00:02:33,666
[METAL MOVING ALONG GROUND]

15
00:02:33,750 --> 00:02:35,000
[GAMBLERBOT B] Hey
we're playing poker over here...

16
00:02:35,083 --> 00:02:36,750
You want in?

17
00:02:36,833 --> 00:02:38,416
No.

18
00:02:38,500 --> 00:02:41,000
Come on! Play a hand!
Just one hand!

19
00:02:41,083 --> 00:02:42,500
I think I'll pass.

20
00:02:42,583 --> 00:02:45,041
[GAMBLERBOT C MAKES
CRAZY NOISES AS HE FALLS]

21
00:02:45,125 --> 00:02:46,500
[GAMBLERBOT C]
Just sit at the table!

22
00:02:46,583 --> 00:02:47,916
Enough.

23
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:50,000
[GAMBLERBOTS ACT
OUT OF CONTROL]

24
00:02:50,083 --> 00:02:51,916
[GAMBLERBOT D LAUGHS]

25
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:53,583
[GAMBLERBOT B]
Play poker.

26
00:02:55,458 --> 00:02:57,083
[GAMBLERBOT C] Win or lose,
it's a game of nerves!

27
00:02:57,166 --> 00:02:59,125
A game that'll test your mettle!

28
00:02:59,208 --> 00:03:00,541
Now play!

29
00:03:00,625 --> 00:03:02,083
[EXPLOSION]

30
00:03:02,166 --> 00:03:04,625
[GAMBLERBOT C LAUGHS]

31
00:03:04,708 --> 00:03:06,291
[IMPACT BLAST]

32
00:03:11,791 --> 00:03:13,166
[GAMBLERBOT C]
Huh?

33
00:03:16,791 --> 00:03:18,500
[GAMBLERBOT C] Let's fight him.
Let's fight him!

34
00:03:18,583 --> 00:03:20,083
Let's fight him!!!

35
00:03:20,166 --> 00:03:22,291
[METAL HAMMERING ON METAL]

36
00:03:22,375 --> 00:03:23,833
[GAMBLERBOT C]
Wait, is that?

37
00:03:23,916 --> 00:03:28,208
[METAL HAMMERING ON METAL]

38
00:03:34,666 --> 00:03:37,625
[GAMBLERBOTS RUN IN FEAR]

39
00:03:39,833 --> 00:03:41,625
I can no longer obtain...

40
00:03:41,708 --> 00:03:44,375
...the proper tools I require.

41
00:03:52,458 --> 00:03:54,708
It's a shame...

42
00:03:54,791 --> 00:03:57,583
There's no good metal
to work with.

43
00:03:59,833 --> 00:04:00,916
You looked...

44
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:04,708
...as if you were
almost dancing before.

45
00:04:04,791 --> 00:04:07,458
Um... And you are?

46
00:04:10,958 --> 00:04:12,541
[LIZBELL]
Sorry.

47
00:04:21,833 --> 00:04:23,041
[CASSHERN]
Who are you?

48
00:04:23,125 --> 00:04:25,625
[LIZBELL] I used to
work at this factory...

49
00:04:25,708 --> 00:04:28,666
...along with everyone else.

50
00:04:28,750 --> 00:04:32,000
[LIZBELL]
We manufactured parts...

51
00:04:32,083 --> 00:04:33,708
...but now...
there's no need to

52
00:04:33,791 --> 00:04:35,291
make anything at alL.

53
00:04:35,375 --> 00:04:37,666
Since there's no work...

54
00:04:37,750 --> 00:04:40,750
...they've resorted to
playing games every day...

55
00:04:40,833 --> 00:04:43,875
...cause... there's simply
nothing better to do.

56
00:04:46,291 --> 00:04:47,833
I, for one, am not content

57
00:04:47,916 --> 00:04:51,166
with sitting idly by
waiting for death.

58
00:04:55,625 --> 00:04:57,625
Not at all.

59
00:05:24,041 --> 00:05:26,583
You interested in
going up there?

60
00:05:38,291 --> 00:05:40,791
The world... spiraling
down towards ruin...

61
00:05:40,875 --> 00:05:43,833
Yet somehow it's so
very... beautiful.

62
00:05:47,916 --> 00:05:49,583
[LIZBELL] It's even more
awe-inspiring

63
00:05:49,666 --> 00:05:54,458
when the sun rises and
sets on the horizon.

64
00:05:54,541 --> 00:05:55,708
[LIZBELL]
Is creating this tower

65
00:05:55,791 --> 00:05:59,000
what you've always
wanted to do?

66
00:06:03,500 --> 00:06:05,291
What's the point?

67
00:06:07,583 --> 00:06:09,541
[LIZBELL]
To ring a bell.

68
00:06:15,333 --> 00:06:16,916
A bell?

69
00:06:21,958 --> 00:06:23,958
[LIZBELL] I want to find
the perfect bell

70
00:06:24,041 --> 00:06:28,333
and attach it to
the top of this tower.

71
00:06:28,416 --> 00:06:31,833
Ding dong... Ding dong...

72
00:06:31,916 --> 00:06:35,458
If I can make the bell
ring loudly enough...

73
00:06:35,541 --> 00:06:37,375
...then, perhaps
I can help people

74
00:06:37,458 --> 00:06:39,875
realize that the world
still holds beauty even

75
00:06:39,958 --> 00:06:42,750
when it is in near
the end of its life.

76
00:06:48,041 --> 00:06:50,000
[LIZBELL]
You're beautiful too.

77
00:07:08,125 --> 00:07:09,708
[CASSHERN STARTLED BY TOUCHING]

78
00:07:09,791 --> 00:07:11,375
[LIZBELL]
Don't move.

79
00:07:16,541 --> 00:07:19,541
You haven't aged...

80
00:07:19,625 --> 00:07:21,083
...as if you're
moving backwards

81
00:07:21,166 --> 00:07:22,791
in time, getting newer.

82
00:07:22,875 --> 00:07:24,708
[CASSHERN SHOCKED]

83
00:07:27,166 --> 00:07:29,708
I can feel it in my fingertips.

84
00:07:37,666 --> 00:07:39,791
[LIZBELL EXHALES]

85
00:07:39,875 --> 00:07:43,125
[LIZBELL]
Ding dong.

86
00:07:43,208 --> 00:07:47,000
Tell me...
Just what are you?

87
00:07:53,708 --> 00:07:55,291
I wish...

88
00:07:56,875 --> 00:07:59,041
I wish I even knew.

89
00:08:19,791 --> 00:08:21,250
I don't quite understand.

90
00:08:21,333 --> 00:08:24,166
What is it that
you want to know?

91
00:08:25,458 --> 00:08:26,750
And why is it that you

92
00:08:26,833 --> 00:08:30,125
seem to be in such immense pain?

93
00:08:33,708 --> 00:08:35,708
[CASSHERN] This is the first
time I've met someone

94
00:08:35,791 --> 00:08:38,041
who believes the
world is beautiful.

95
00:08:41,416 --> 00:08:43,208
[CASSHERN] When
you finish your bell...

96
00:08:43,291 --> 00:08:46,250
...I hope I'll
be able to hear it.

97
00:08:51,666 --> 00:08:56,000
[LIZBELL] Then please,
do me this one favor.

98
00:08:56,083 --> 00:08:57,875
Don't leave yet.

99
00:09:02,750 --> 00:09:06,333
The bell...
will be finished soon.

100
00:09:06,416 --> 00:09:08,000
[LIZBELL CHUCKLES SLYLY]

101
00:09:45,583 --> 00:09:47,041
One of the hardest aspects

102
00:09:47,125 --> 00:09:48,458
of this was finding suitable

103
00:09:48,541 --> 00:09:50,791
parts for the bell's casting...

104
00:09:50,875 --> 00:09:54,791
Ideally... I would prefer
gold or silver for this...

105
00:09:54,875 --> 00:09:56,000
only...

106
00:09:56,083 --> 00:09:59,041
...those don't exist anymore.

107
00:10:01,291 --> 00:10:04,708
But... today I have finally
amassed enough materials

108
00:10:04,791 --> 00:10:08,458
to finish the bell... at last.

109
00:10:13,958 --> 00:10:15,666
[LIZBELL]
I've been waiting...

110
00:10:15,750 --> 00:10:17,416
...for you I suppose...

111
00:10:17,500 --> 00:10:20,250
...and for the perfect moment.

112
00:10:24,166 --> 00:10:26,208
The scented candles...

113
00:10:26,291 --> 00:10:28,250
I can smell it.

114
00:10:29,875 --> 00:10:31,458
That's right.

115
00:10:54,083 --> 00:10:56,541
[LIZBELL SIGHS SEDUCTIVELY]

116
00:10:56,625 --> 00:10:58,250
[CASSHERN GASPS]

117
00:11:27,958 --> 00:11:29,541
[LIZBELL CHUCKLES]

118
00:11:39,916 --> 00:11:42,875
[METAL GEARS SLOWLY GRIND]

119
00:11:44,416 --> 00:11:47,375
[LIZBELL LETS OUT A
SIGH AND THEN LAUGHS]

120
00:11:48,583 --> 00:11:53,541
[METAL GEARS GRINDING
A LITTLE FASTER]

121
00:12:08,791 --> 00:12:12,083
[METAL COLLISION
AND METAL STRAINING]

122
00:12:12,166 --> 00:12:16,166
[BLAST AND AN ESCAPE OF STEAM]

123
00:12:23,666 --> 00:12:24,916
Let me guess,

124
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:27,833
you were pretending to be
asleep this entire time.

125
00:12:32,375 --> 00:12:33,416
You do realize you

126
00:12:33,500 --> 00:12:35,791
will be a permanent
part of this bell.

127
00:12:35,875 --> 00:12:38,500
[LIZBELL] You're not serving a
purpose otherwise, are you...?

128
00:12:38,583 --> 00:12:40,708
So help me out
and become the bell.

129
00:12:40,791 --> 00:12:44,625
It's better than dying
in a scrap-yard, right?

130
00:12:44,708 --> 00:12:46,250
That's what I had thought...

131
00:12:46,333 --> 00:12:48,000
...that it would be better to...

132
00:12:48,083 --> 00:12:50,250
...become part of the bell
and ring out to the land

133
00:12:50,333 --> 00:12:52,291
in a positive light...

134
00:12:52,375 --> 00:12:55,333
...but I'm not ready to do that.

135
00:12:57,208 --> 00:12:58,333
[CASSHERN] I am the
one who killed

136
00:12:58,416 --> 00:13:00,625
the Sun that was named Moon...

137
00:13:00,708 --> 00:13:04,083
...and I still have
some unfinished business.

138
00:13:04,166 --> 00:13:05,000
[CASSHERN]
Much in the same way

139
00:13:05,083 --> 00:13:08,041
you desire to create your bell.

140
00:13:30,791 --> 00:13:34,416
[LIZBELL] All I want...
is to hear it ring...

141
00:13:34,500 --> 00:13:37,625
I want the people to hear it.

142
00:13:37,708 --> 00:13:39,666
I want to believe...

143
00:13:39,750 --> 00:13:42,416
...that there is beauty
in this dying world...

144
00:13:42,500 --> 00:13:44,958
...and I want
others to believe...

145
00:13:45,041 --> 00:13:46,083
...even the robots who've

146
00:13:46,166 --> 00:13:48,958
resorted to
gambling all the time.

147
00:13:51,250 --> 00:13:55,875
All robots...
have a desire to survive...

148
00:13:55,958 --> 00:13:59,458
Even those robots you
scrapped so selfishly...

149
00:13:59,541 --> 00:14:02,500
Did their desires
cross your mind?

150
00:14:18,791 --> 00:14:21,583
[STEAM ESCAPING]

151
00:14:24,708 --> 00:14:27,666
[EXPULSION OF HOT METAL]

152
00:14:53,166 --> 00:14:56,125
[BELL TOLLING]

153
00:15:04,583 --> 00:15:06,833
What was that sound?

154
00:15:06,916 --> 00:15:09,875
[BELL TOLLING]

155
00:15:30,791 --> 00:15:33,750
[BELL TOLLING]

156
00:15:41,416 --> 00:15:44,375
[LIZBELL GASPS AS SHE FALLS]

157
00:15:46,875 --> 00:15:50,125
[LIZBELL] The sound...
it's not enough.

158
00:15:58,666 --> 00:16:01,625
[LIZBELL STRUGGLES]
[BELL TOLLS]

159
00:16:18,750 --> 00:16:20,958
[LIZBELL STRUGGLES]
[BELL TOLLS]

160
00:16:21,041 --> 00:16:22,291
[METAL ROBOTS
CLANKING UP THE STAIRS]

161
00:16:24,208 --> 00:16:25,500
[GAMBLERBOT D] Lizbell!
[GAMBLERBOT B]The Witch!

162
00:16:25,583 --> 00:16:27,208
[GAMBLERBOT C] Quiet!

163
00:16:27,916 --> 00:16:29,166
[CRASH]

164
00:16:29,250 --> 00:16:32,208
[LIZBELL STRUGGLES]
[BELL TOLLS]

165
00:16:33,166 --> 00:16:35,083
[GAMBLERBOT C] Quiet.

166
00:16:35,166 --> 00:16:35,916
[GLASS BREAKING]

167
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:37,291
[ROBOT CLANKING]

168
00:16:37,375 --> 00:16:39,208
[GAMBLERBOT C]
Shut up...! Shut up!

169
00:16:39,291 --> 00:16:40,916
[GAMBLERBOT C]
Shut up...! Shut up!

170
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:43,500
Shut up! Shut up!

171
00:16:43,583 --> 00:16:46,750
Shut up! Shut up!

172
00:16:46,833 --> 00:16:50,166
[METAL BREAKING
AND ROBOT YELLING]

173
00:16:50,250 --> 00:16:52,208
[GAMBLERBOT C]
My hand! This is your fault!

174
00:16:52,291 --> 00:16:55,416
You built this stupid thing.

175
00:16:55,500 --> 00:16:58,666
[GAMBLERBOT C YELLS GIBBERISH]

176
00:16:58,750 --> 00:17:00,375
[GAMBLERBOT C] The whole
world's gonna be ruined

177
00:17:00,458 --> 00:17:04,208
so building this
thing was useless!

178
00:17:04,291 --> 00:17:06,083
[LIZBELL]
You're right.

179
00:17:06,916 --> 00:17:08,416
[LIZBELL]
It was a waste.

180
00:17:08,500 --> 00:17:15,166
[CRASHING]

181
00:17:19,125 --> 00:17:23,083
[METAL CREAKS AND BELL TOLLS]
[BUILDING IMPLODES]

182
00:17:26,583 --> 00:17:28,625
[GLASS BREAKS]

183
00:17:28,708 --> 00:17:30,666
[IMPACT BLAST]

184
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:34,958
[IMPACT BLAST]

185
00:17:42,750 --> 00:17:45,750
[METAL CLANKING]

186
00:17:45,833 --> 00:17:48,500
[GAMBLERBOT C]
I got three pair.

187
00:17:56,791 --> 00:18:00,750
[CASSHERN STRUGGLES]

188
00:18:01,416 --> 00:18:04,083
[LIZBELL GASPS WITH PAIN]

189
00:18:13,208 --> 00:18:16,000
It's you again.

190
00:18:16,083 --> 00:18:18,833
It sounded just fine.

191
00:18:20,291 --> 00:18:22,250
Who cares?

192
00:18:25,041 --> 00:18:27,458
[CASSHERN] I felt it
when you rang the bell...

193
00:18:27,541 --> 00:18:30,125
...resounding in my heart.

194
00:18:30,208 --> 00:18:34,833
[LIZBELL] Liar... It was
a terrible sound.

195
00:18:34,916 --> 00:18:36,041
That's not true...

196
00:18:36,125 --> 00:18:38,250
I think it resonated in
my heart because

197
00:18:38,333 --> 00:18:39,291
you were able to create

198
00:18:39,375 --> 00:18:42,291
something new in
this desolate world.

199
00:18:48,291 --> 00:18:50,458
When I heard the bell ring...

200
00:18:50,541 --> 00:18:52,250
...for the first time...

201
00:18:52,333 --> 00:18:55,000
...I felt beauty
all around me...

202
00:18:55,083 --> 00:18:58,750
...in a world that
I have driven into ruin.

203
00:19:07,208 --> 00:19:09,000
Casshern!

204
00:19:31,375 --> 00:19:34,208
[RINGO LAUGHS]

205
00:19:34,291 --> 00:19:37,250
[RINGO EXPRESSES AMAZEMENT]

206
00:19:45,666 --> 00:19:47,916
[RINGO]
What is that tower for?

207
00:19:48,791 --> 00:19:50,583
No idea.

208
00:19:53,291 --> 00:19:56,083
Would you like
to go to the top?

209
00:19:58,541 --> 00:20:02,208
If you're interested I could
take you all the way up.

210
00:20:07,541 --> 00:20:11,500
[RINGO MAKES PLAYFUL
NOISES AND LAUGHS]

211
00:20:20,833 --> 00:20:22,791
Look at the view!

212
00:20:25,916 --> 00:20:29,000
[OHJI]
Be careful now, Ringo.

213
00:20:29,083 --> 00:20:31,333
Wow Ohji... look at how

214
00:20:31,416 --> 00:20:34,000
pretty the Earth is from here.

215
00:20:34,083 --> 00:20:36,625
[OHJI GRUNTS IN AGREEMENT]

216
00:20:36,708 --> 00:20:39,000
Would you like
to give it a ring?

217
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:50,791
There is a bell...
suspended from up there.

218
00:21:05,166 --> 00:21:08,875
Ding dong... Ding dong...

219
00:21:08,958 --> 00:21:13,041
Ding dong... Ding dong.

220
00:21:16,333 --> 00:21:19,125
I don't... need
the actual bell...

221
00:21:19,208 --> 00:21:23,166
...when I can let it ring in
my heart from now on.

222
00:21:24,583 --> 00:21:28,541
[LIZBELL]
Ding dong...

223
00:21:44,875 --> 00:21:47,166
[CASSHERN] There was a woman who
built a tower so she could

224
00:21:47,250 --> 00:21:48,583
ring a bell for the ruined

225
00:21:48,666 --> 00:21:50,500
world to hear...

226
00:21:50,583 --> 00:21:52,625
That sound still resonates...

227
00:21:52,708 --> 00:21:54,666
...in my ears.

228
00:21:56,583 --> 00:22:00,875
[LIZBELL]
Ding dong. Ding dong.

229
00:22:02,416 --> 00:22:07,375
♪ ENDING SONG ♪

230
00:23:34,041 --> 00:23:36,875
[CASSHERN] There was a woman
who gave hope to others...

231
00:23:36,958 --> 00:23:41,250
...while she herself ruined away
in this hopeless world.

232
00:23:41,333 --> 00:23:45,000
Next time...
a Hymn of Hope.

